steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Separate the leaves from the endive
- Halve the pear lengthwise, core it and thinly slice it
- Shave the Piave cheese
- Finely grate the garlic clove

### Veggies
1. Trim stems of vegetables
2. Cut out core of cauliflower (if using)
3. Thinly slice vegetables crosswise about " thick
4. Toss vegetables, endive, pear, and cheese in a large bowl
5. Add oil and 1 Tbsp. fresh lemon juice; season with sea salt and pepper
6. Using your hands, toss salad until well coated
7. Chill (uncovered is fine) while you prepare the dressing

### Dressing
1. Whisk yogurt, mayonnaise, garlic, lemon zest, and remaining 2 Tbsp. lemon juice in a small bowl; season with kosher salt

### Assembly
1. Arrange about one-quarter of salad on a large platter
2. Drizzle some dressing over, letting it fall into the nooks and crannies of the vegetables
3. Add another one-quarter of salad; drizzle with dressing in same manner
4. Repeat with remaining salad and dressing
5. Season with kosher salt and pepper

ingredients.note: Ex cauliflower, fennel bulbs, daikon radishes, and or turnips
Or Firm Bosc Pear, Halved lengthwise, cored, thinly sliced
